We performed a topic search regarding 17 SDGs and SVI in the Web of Science database on 1st May 2022 (Table 1
                     ). Although the 2030 Agenda was launched in 2015, some studies published before 2015 were also included as the UN and some countries have devoted their efforts to promoting sustainable development since 1992 (Desa, 2016). We followed the Preferred Reporting Items for Systematic Reviews and meta-Analyses (Liberati et al., 2009) for the study selection (Fig. 1
                     ).

The selected studies were conducted in 18 countries, mainly from Asia and North America, and no studies were conducted in Africa (
                        Fig. 3

                        ). China and the United States (US) are the top two study areas. The studies in China mainly focus on SDG 11 (nÂ =Â 37) and 3 (nÂ =Â 27), among which there are five studies on SDG 13. The proportions of research topics conducted in the US showed a similar pattern (30 on SDG 11, 10 on SDG 3, and one on SDG 13), including one study on SDG 2. Studies mainly focus on SDG 11 in other countries. In addition, almost all studies were conducted at the neighborhood and city scales, with only a few at the country scale.
